<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What is the most impportant skill to start on?<P>Why?<P>What % of xp should I donate to skill advancement?  I was thinking 10%.<P>Any info helpful!<P>Dannig<P>------------------<BR>Dannig   55 Cleric<BR>Dark Elf<BR>Member of The Commune <BR>Xegony<P>group01 "Dannig, heal yourself"<BR>you tell the group "Oh yeah  :) "</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kornaena</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am thinking 0% to you reach level 60.  That is unless you have no need to reach 60. The spells you get as you level to 60 far outweight any marginal skins you get.  Reaching 60 have more benefit than sidetracking exp to abilities.<p>[This message has been edited by Kornaena (edited 12-06-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I fully agree.<P>Get level 60 before worrying about skills.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4264" TARGET=_blank>Mikar of the Nexus</A><BR>High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/" TARGET=_blank>The Companions</A><BR>The Tribunal</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Havdin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't think there is a right answer to those questions Dannig.  Given how slowly I level I would probably put 10% to 20% into these just so that I can start picking up some skills before I ever hit level 60.  I mean some of those skills could be useful enough to have right away as opposed to waiting later.<P>If I was a hardcore player and leveled very quickly I would probably wait till 60 first then go 100% into alternate skills.<P>I do kind of like the fact that this alternate advancement will allow me to keep from outleveling my regular grouping partners though.  I'll be able to go group with other people and divert most or all of it to gaining ablilities and not feel guilty for gaining exp quicklier than they are.  Something else to consider it you have people you wish to stay around level-wise with.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Havdin:<BR><B>I mean some of those skills could be useful enough to have right away as opposed to waiting later.<BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Actually they will not be more useful. Gaining levels is SO much more useful than any skills you are gonna get. More HPs, better resist, larger mana pool, BETTER SPELLS, etc.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Havdin:<BR><B>I do kind of like the fact that this alternate advancement will allow me to keep from outleveling my regular grouping partners though. I'll be able to go group with other people and divert most or all of it to gaining ablilities and not feel guilty for gaining exp quicklier than they are. <BR></B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Thats not gonna make that much of a difference past 50th to worry about. If you are that concerned about it, i recommend getting pratically all of your exp bar filled for that level, then divert all to skills till they catch up (which wont take long)<P>Its your exps to do with as you will, but frankly its a waste until you get to 60th. <BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Havdin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah probably.  I'm just trying to remain open minded about these skills.  I'll never know till I atually try them.  Part of it is do I have the patience to reach level 60 first or not.  Knowing myself, probably not.   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Adon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">On the other hand, for those of us with Naggy/Vox Alts (52 and under) we can switch to skills exp at 52...<P>And make em uber 52 twinks to kick some dragon arse!<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goryn Grimblade</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I must disagree with most of the previous posters.  While a lot of the skills are rather trivial, some could prove quite useful much before we reach 60.  Excluding the class-specific skills, since you need to be 59, there are many of the Healer-specific skills that could greatly benefit a non-uber cleric.<P>Certainly Mental Clarity is of use to everyone, since unless I really miss it we still do not possess self mana regen.  I realize there are many Flowing Thought items out there but why not have an innate abilty to regen, thus giving you more item flexibility?  Even the Generic ability regen would be a nice addition, though definitely more for a tank than us.  The critical heal thing is decent, at least in terms of healing anyone but a main tank (CH would waste it I imagine).  The spell casting improvements could potentially help a lot, depending on how often they really work (only VI knows for sure).  I can't remember the others right now, but as I have had some major PC problems lately those have been on my mind more than EQ  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif">.<P>Though I am only 56, I plan to keep my experience between 50/50 and 70/30 in favor of leveling.  This goes against what I hear from many people, but I really think its a better way.  I never expected to level this high, so anything I continue to get is gravy to me.<P>------------------<BR>Fare thee well,<P><B>Goryn Grymblade</B><BR>Templar of Drinal<BR><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/bloodhonorguild" TARGET=_blank>Blood Honor Guild</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In most cases I'd say 0% to alt XP until you're 60 (understand where you're coming from though, Goryn).<P>In my case however, I've only got about 7 blues to go till 60, so I decided to put 20% to alt for yesterday evening's XP camping (some in Fungus Grove, some in The Deep).<P>3 hours of fighting at 80/20 netted me just over a blue of regular XP and 1.5 blues of alt XP, which is pretty good going.  If I'd gone 100% altadv, I'd be 1.5 yellows in.<P>So it looks like this alternate advancement is going to be reasonably painless - maybe 10 hours of XP camping per skill point?<P>It also looks like Luclin's a pretty nice place for general XP camping: I've only really fought in FG, The Deep & The Grey so far, but the mobs certainly feel a lot easier than Velious mobs of a similar level.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>59th level Templar of Bristlebane<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kaharz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/shrug well I'm with the "not really worth it till 60 crowd," But to each their own.<P>I looked over the skills, and some are really nice, but I'm 53rd and lvl slow.  I'm just about the lowest person in my guild since the cap got raised to 55 (exceptions are made of course) about two months ago.  I've made oh I think a yellow and a half since then  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>As far as I'm concerned it looks like the most important ones, are healing efficiency (don't remember if that is what it's called but it gives us +% to heal spells), and the buff duration, mass group buff ones.<P>The less you have to cast buffs, definately the more mana (and dots) you are going to save.  Mental Clarity would be very nice too, but considering in grinds I'm almost never out of mana, and on raids I usually have C2, bard song, and necros and mages when rushed it's not that big of a worry.  On a raid like a Kael areana or whatever, I almost never have to heal enough to call for a med break.  And in a raid like HoT in ToV, I have to take extra time to med frequently, but hte puller is usually spending most that time getting the next pull set up anyway.  Yea, I've had to call a wait in ToV before to med up, but I've also sat there with full mana, waiting for some roamers to move too.  /shrug<P>Some of the skills are really nice, and most the rest are definately worthwhile, I dunno if they are worth it till I get to 60 though.<P>Kaharz Stronginthearm<BR>53rd lvl Vicar of Brell<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR>Forsaken<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
